<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-10-07T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-10-07T16:00:00-05:00" n="551" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d551">
                                <note rend="inline" type="source">765.84/1640: Telegram</note>
                                <head>
                                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gilbert</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                            State</gloss>
                                    </hi>
                                </head>
                                <opener>
                                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                                        <placeName>
                                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-10-07T22:00:00+01:00">October 7, 1935—10 p.m.</date>
                                        <lb/> [Received October 8—12:26 a.m.]</dateline>
                                </opener>
                                <p>442. A communiqué was issued this afternoon giving the following
                                    text of a telegram dated October 7 from the Ethiopian Foreign
                                    Minister to the Secretary General: <quote rend="blockquote">
                                        <p>“Italian troops escorted by 20 airplanes entered Aduwa
                                            yesterday without resistance after taking Adigrat. Our
                                            troops which were outside the town of Aduwa are still
                                            there. All engagements hitherto have been with our
                                            frontier guard and small isolated detachments. Our
                                            troops have not yet gone into action. Italian
                                            aggression, in preparation for several months against
                                            Ethiopia which has been systematically refused arms for
                                            its defense, has thus been carried into effect in a
                                            district where the frontier has been clearly defined by
                                            the treaties and is therefore indisputable.”</p>
                                    </quote>
                                </p>
                                <closer>
                                    <signed>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Gilbert</hi>
                                    </signed>
                                </closer>
                            </div>
                            </body></text></TEI>